caption: The guy who answers the phone for orders is so rude. I called to order a jade smoothie for pickup on 3/16/21. he tells me to hold on and hangs up the phone. Ordered here on UberEats and it was well worth the wait. I've had a lot of salads, but this is one of the BEST salads I've ever had. The kale was tender and massaged (this makes it tender and easier to digest) a lot of other places that have kale greens in their salads miss that step.  The portion was huge and I had more than enough chicken (protein) for saving the second 1/2 of the salad for dinner later. Also, I got a green juice and it was extremely fresh and delicious. I will be ordering here again!

So today I ordered online for the first time from Twisted Rootz. Everything was correct but the chicken was missing. I was just gonna write a bad review but the presentation was so nice and neat that I knew it had to be a mistake. The owner asked zero questions and was QUICK to fix it. She sent someone to my house with an OVERLY generous amount of chicken for my salad.  The chicken was juicy, BOMB and worth the wait! And the smoothies ... amazing!!! They made a fan and a customer out of me! And I found out they are black HAITIAN owned! 🇭🇹🇭🇹 The best thing I've discovered since moving to Canarsie! I love it here!

We decided to take the 35 minute drive from our home in Queens on a Sunday afternoon to get lunch at Twisted Roots on a recommendation and from the  great reviews found here... we were not disappointed! We ordered 3 smoothies, I had the #15 and added watermelon... Tasted so FRESH, REFRESHING, and Delicious! I also ordered a jerk chicken Panini... quite possibly the best Panini I've ever had... Super flavorful, really good.  The customer service, cleanliness and food all get an A++. Would DEFINITELY recommend you try it out if you've never been, I would definitely be a regular customer of I lived closer... so glad we made the trip, we'll be back!

I had a great experience here at Twisted Rootz. Customer service here is amazing. As soon as I walked in I was greeted with smiles and the workers welcoming me to Twisted Rootz. Their menu is just full of fresh healthy options I ordered a strawberry peach mango smoothie it was AMAZING. I created my own curry chicken rice bowl. After tasting that smoothie I couldn't wait to see what's my food would taste like, and The smell of fresh curry filling the restaurant made me anticipate my food even more. Once I got my food my I was beyond satisfied. The workers made sure I had everything down to salt and pepper in my bag like they really took care of me like I was one of their friends and not just another dollar sign like some of those other restaurants on that flatlands strip, And once I got to eat my food every taste bud on my tongue was jumping in excitement. We need more restaurants like this in the neighborhood. An establishment that appreciates the customers that supports them. They make it clear US THE CUSTOMERS is the reason they are open and they appreciate every bit of it. They earned that five star rating and I expect them to grow into a full blown dine in restaurant in the future In the city showing them other restaurants how customer service is done. Thank you Twisted Rootz  -Q
